'''Davod Jon''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Colonel/Legends|colonel]] who served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] as a [[Imperial Special Forces/Legends|Special Forces]] leader in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Jon was promoted for his skills and bravery as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]]. In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], Jon was present for the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] arrival aboard the Empire's [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]], and afterward for the arrival of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Jon would serve under [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Firmus Piett/Legends|Firmus Piett]] during the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

==Biography==
Davod Jon was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] who served as a [[Colonel/Legends|colonel]] in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].<ref name="CCG1" /> As an [[Imperial officer/Legends|officer]] of the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial Army]], Jon was promoted for his skills and bravery as a [[Scout/Legends|scout]].<ref name="CSWE" /> He served as a leader<ref name="CCG1" /> in the Empire's [[Imperial Special Forces/Legends|Special Forces]] unit.<ref name="CSWE" />

Shortly before the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]<ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] to the beginning of [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> Jon was among the many Imperial personnel present when the [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] arrived aboard the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] to coerce the [[Battle station/Legends|battle station's]] commander, [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Tiaan Jerjerrod/Legends|Tiaan Jerjerrod]], to quicken the [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon's]] construction, to which Jerjerrod responded that his construction crews would double their efforts.<ref name="ROTJ" /> Afterward, Jon stood in one of the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star's]] [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]] bays alongside Vader and other [[Officer/Legends|officers]] to await the arrival of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] aboard the battlestation.<ref name="Topps">{{Topps|set=1983 Topps Star Wars: Return of the Jedi Series 1|cardname=On the Death Star|link=https://www.tcdb.com/ViewCard.cfm/sid/72969/cid/5256904/1983-Topps-Return-Of-The-Jedi-54-On-the-Death-Star}}</ref> Jon went on to serve under [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Firmus Piett/Legends|Firmus Piett]],<ref name="CSWE" /> the [[Commanding officer/Legends|commanding officer]] of the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|Star Dreadnought]] [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']] and [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron]],<ref name="db">{{DB|character|admiralpiett|Piett, Admiral}}</ref> Vader's personal [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]],<ref name="ISD Encyclopedia">{{SWE|technology|imperialstardestroyer|Imperial Star Destroyer}}</ref> during the Battle of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]].<ref name="CSWE" />

==Personality and traits==
Davod Jon was known as a proficient leader. Despite the Empire's obvious technological superiority over opponents, Jon advocated the development of wilderness survival training for Imperial [[Troop/Legends|troops]]<ref name="CSWE" /> and convinced his superiors that wilderness survival and recon training were also necessary for military dominance.<ref name="CCG1" />

Jon had [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] that was graying with age and light skin.<ref name="CCG1" />

==Equipment==
Colonel Jon wore the standard-issue [[Imperial officer's uniform/Legends|Imperial officer's uniform]].<ref name="ROTJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:MoffJerjerrodGreetsVader.jpg|thumb|right|300px|A scene from the ''Special Edition'' of ''The Empire Strikes Back'', reused from Vader's arrival on the Death Star in ''Return of the Jedi'']]
Davod Jon first appeared as one of the many Imperial personnel awaiting [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vader's arrival on the second Death Star in the opening scene of [[1983]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. The character was portrayed by an uncredited actor,<ref name="ROTJ" /> and was later on given a name and a brief backstory in the [[2000]] ''[[Death Star II Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG1" />

[http://www.starwarz.com/tbone/index.php?categoryid=11&p2_articleid=5 Several images] found on [http://www.starwarz.com/tbone/index.php?categoryid=1 T-bone's Star Wars Universe] fan Web site show that Davod Jon was meant to appear in at least one additional scene in ''Return of the Jedi'', which did not make the final cut. The last two out of six images from the previous link are from the beginning of an extended version of the [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor's]] arrival aboard the second Death Star from a scene later in the movie, and the penultimate image shows Jon as part of a group of officers standing in a docking bay to greet Palpatine.<ref name="T-bone">{{WebCite|url=http://www.starwarz.com/tbone/index.php?categoryid=11&p2_articleid=5|text=T-bone's Star Wars Universe - Return of the Jedi - Off To See The Emperor|author=T-bone|date=2003-06-03|work=T-bone's Star Wars Universe|archivedate=20071112111838}}</ref>

Original footage depicting Vader's arrival aboard the Death Star in the opening scene of ''Return of the Jedi'' was reused for the [[1997]] [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|''Special Edition'']] release of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] to show Vader arriving aboard his [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]], the ''Executor'', following his [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City]] [[Duel on Cloud City/Legends|duel]] with [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. As such, the extras who portrayed the Imperial personnel awaiting Vader's Death Star arrival in ''Return of the Jedi'', including Jon's actor, can be seen in ''The Empire Strikes Back'' ''Special Edition''.<ref name="ESB">{{Film|V}}</ref> However, the Davod Jon character is not [[canon]]ically established to have been aboard the ''Executor'' in the reused scene.

